  "text_preview": "\"monkey\" American Sign Language (ASL) ASL Lessons | Bookstore | Library | ASL University Main ► MONKEY : The American Sign Language (ASL) sign for \"monkey\" The sign for \"monkey\" is easy to do -- just act like one. Scratch your sides twice. MONKEY: Sample sentence: MONKEY CLIMB TREE CAN? (Can monkeys climb trees?) If you want to learn more animal signs, check out: Notes: For a discussion regarding how to sign specific types of primates, see: MONKEY (advanced) Also see: APE ANIMALS * Want to help support ASL University? It's easy : DONATE ( Thanks! ) * Another way to help is to buy something from Dr. Bill's \" Bookstore .\" * Want even more ASL resources? Visit the \" ASL Training Center ! \" (Subscription Extension of ASLU) * Also check out Dr. Bill's channel: www.youtube.com/billvicars You can"
}
